(Falcon-512 Integration Notes and Audit) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Status: Alpha documentation snapshot \(2026-03-12\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This explains how Falcon-512 is integrated into the Atho stack, where signing and verification) Tj
T*
(happen, how keys are handled, and the security posture of the current implementation \(excluding) Tj
T*
(the C source itself under Src/Falcon/Falcon\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Related reference package: Docs/falcon Docs.pdf \(NIST/Falcon context used by this repo\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Components \(code paths\)) Tj
T*
(- Binary: platform-tagged binaries live under) Tj
T*
(Src/Falcon/Binaries/<platform_tag>/falcon_cli\(.exe\) with legacy fallback to) Tj
T*
(Src/Falcon/Falcon/falcon_cli. Build script: Src/Falcon/Falcon/compile_falcon.sh; registration) Tj
T*
(script: Src/Falcon/Falcon/install_platform_binary.py.) Tj
T*
(- Wrapper: Src/Accounts/falconcli.py locates the binary, enforces strict version-bound pinning) Tj
T*
(on required networks \(FALCONCLI_PIN_DOMAIN, FALCONCLI_PIN_REQUIRED_NETWORKS,) Tj
T*
(FALCONCLI_PINNED_VERSION_DIGESTS\), validates it \(runs keygen\), and exposes keygen, sign, and) Tj
T*
(verify helpers. Optional FFI verify fallback via FALCON_VERIFY_SO.) Tj
T*
(- Key manager: Src/Accounts/key_manager.py calls FalconCLI for keygen/sign/verify, enforces) Tj
T*
(CLI-format keys, and stores them in JSON \(default Keys/KeyManager_Public_Private_Keys.json\). It) Tj
T*
(derives hashed public keys \(HPK\) and Base56 addresses from the Falcon public key.) Tj
T*
(- Transaction hashing: Src/Utility/txdhash.py defines canonical_tx_id \(no-witness hash\) and) Tj
T*
(signing_message_hex_digest \(sha3_384 of canonical fields\) used for signing and verification.) Tj
T*
(- Transaction signing: Src/Main/send.py and Src/Transactions/tx.py build txs, then call) Tj
T*
(KeyManager.sign_transaction, which in turn invokes FalconCLI.sign on the signing digest.) Tj
T*
(- Transaction verification: Src/Transactions/txvalidation.py::_validate_signature strips witness) Tj
T*
(data \(SegWit.strip_witness\), recomputes the signing digest, and calls) Tj
T*
(KeyManager.verify_transaction, which uses FalconCLI.verify/verify_transaction_hash \(multiple) Tj
T*
(call orders + optional FFI\).) Tj
T*
(- Block validation: Src/Main/blockveri.py trusts TXValidation for per-tx signature checks;) Tj
T*
(coinbase has no signature.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key and signature formats) Tj
T*
(- Public key: Falcon-512, 1024 bytes = 2048 hex chars. Private key components f/g/F/G: 1793) Tj
T*
(bytes each = 3586 hex chars.) Tj
T*
(- Signatures: treated as 2048 hex chars \(1024 bytes\). Verification accepts 1024 or 2048 hex) Tj
T*
(length.) Tj
T*
(- Wire format: transaction witness fields \(pubkey, signature\) are canonical base64) Tj
T*
(on-chain/wire; they are decoded back to hex/bytes before Falcon verification.) Tj
T*
(- Hashing/signing payload: sha3_384 digest \(96 hex chars\) of the canonical no-witness) Tj
T*
(transaction body from signing_message_hex_digest. Witness \(tx.signature\) is **not** included in) Tj
T*
(the txid.) Tj
T*
(- Address binding: outputs carry hashed_public_key \(HPK\); HPK is derived from the Falcon public) Tj
T*
(key and can be rendered as Base56 via Src/Blockchain/base56.py.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Binary discovery and hardening \(Src/Accounts/falconcli.py\)) Tj
T*
(- Path search order: provided cli_path ? ATHO_FALCONCLI_BIN env override ? PATH \(falcon_cli\) ?) Tj
T*
(platform-tagged candidates in Src/Falcon/Binaries/ ? legacy Src/Falcon/Falcon/falcon_cli.) Tj
T*
(- Hash pinning: preferred path is version-bound pinning) Tj
T*
(\(FALCONCLI_PINNED_VERSION_DIGESTS[CONSENSUS_VERSION]\); legacy raw-binary pinning) Tj
T*
(\(FALCONCLI_EXPECTED_HASH\) is a fallback.) Tj
T*
ET
