(- Startup validation: supports mode-controlled CLI sanity checks:) Tj
T*
(- ATHO_FALCONCLI_VALIDATE_MODE=cached \(default\): validate once per binary fingerprint) Tj
T*
(\(path+mtime+size+expected hash\), then reuse cache.) Tj
T*
(- ATHO_FALCONCLI_VALIDATE_MODE=always: validate on every process init.) Tj
T*
(- ATHO_FALCONCLI_VALIDATE_MODE=off: skip startup validation.) Tj
T*
(- Cached validation state is persisted to logs/falconcli/validation_cache.json \(override with) Tj
T*
(ATHO_FALCONCLI_VALIDATE_CACHE\).) Tj
T*
(- Rebuild fallback still applies for exec format errors.) Tj
T*
(- Optional FFI verify: loads FALCON_VERIFY_SO \(or sibling libfalcon_verify.*\) and, if present,) Tj
T*
(uses CLI first, then FFI falcon_verify\(pub, msg48, sig\) on failure.) Tj
T*
(- Temp handling: signing now uses in-memory key delivery via stdin \(falcon_cli sign --key-stdin) Tj
T*
(<msg_hex>\), so private key parts are not written to a temporary file on disk.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Signing flow \(tx creation\)) Tj
T*
(- Send.send resolves sender HPK ? key identifier via KeyManager.) Tj
T*
(- Tx is built without signatures; txid/no-witness hash set.) Tj
T*
(- KeyManager.sign_transaction:) Tj
T*
(- Normalizes the signing message to hex \(detects 48-byte raw or 96-char hex SHA3-384\).) Tj
T*
(- Extracts CLI-format private key \(f/g/F/G\).) Tj
T*
(- Calls FalconCLI.sign\(priv, message_hex\) ? signature hex.) Tj
T*
(- Returns bytes \(decoded from hex\) to the caller.) Tj
T*
(- The witness signature/public key are stored in tx witness fields and encoded as canonical) Tj
T*
(base64 when serialized \(Transaction.to_dict\).) Tj
T*
(- Inputs reference prev outputs via tx_out_id and carry only compact SIG_REF markers \(no full) Tj
T*
(embedded signature\).) Tj
T*
(- Size/fee recalculated after witness is added \(policy uses canonical vsize\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Verification flow \(tx admission\)) Tj
T*
(- TXValidation.normalize_tx_dict standardizes shapes and derives prev_tx_id/index.) Tj
T*
(- SegWit.strip_witness removes signature/pubkey to get the base tx for hashing.) Tj
T*
(- signing_message_hex_digest recomputes the signing payload \(sha3_384 hex\).) Tj
T*
(- KeyManager.verify_transaction:) Tj
T*
(- Resolves pubkey from identifier/HPK; recomputes HPK to ensure binding.) Tj
T*
(- Normalizes message to hex \(prefers 96-char sha3_384 if present\).) Tj
T*
(- Normalizes signature \(hex or base64\).) Tj
T*
(- Runs FalconCLI.verify \(CLI\), then verify-hex, then manual CLI orders; optional FFI fallback if) Tj
T*
(configured.) Tj
T*
(- On success, validation continues to fee/UTXO checks; on failure, tx is rejected.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Build & runtime requirements) Tj
T*
(- falcon_cli must be executable for the host \(x86_64/ARM\). Rebuild with) Tj
T*
(Src/Falcon/Falcon/compile_falcon.sh or the inline gcc/clang command in falconcli.py.) Tj
T*
(- Set execute bit: chmod +x Src/Falcon/Falcon/falcon_cli.) Tj
T*
(- If signing fails with --key-stdin unsupported, you are running an older falcon_cli; rebuild) Tj
T*
(from current cli.c and refresh pinned digest constants before main/test/reg runtime use.) Tj
T*
(- Optional env:) Tj
T*
(- FALCON_VERIFY_SO for FFI verify.) Tj
T*
(- FALCONCLI_SILENT=1 to mute verbose logs.) Tj
T*
(- ATHO_FALCONCLI_VALIDATE_MODE \(cached|always|off\) for startup validation behavior.) Tj
T*
(- ATHO_FALCONCLI_VALIDATE_CACHE to override startup validation cache file location.) Tj
T*
(- Hash pin: maintain Constants.FALCONCLI_PINNED_VERSION_DIGESTS_BY_PLATFORM +) Tj
T*
(Constants.FALCONCLI_EXPECTED_HASH_BY_PLATFORM for release builds. Use global pins only as) Tj
