(fallback.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Audit findings / risks) Tj
T*
(- Hash pinning is **required on mainnet/testnet by default**; startup fails if no expected) Tj
T*
(digest is configured for the active consensus version. Keep the digest map current for every) Tj
T*
(release.) Tj
T*
(- FFI fallback will load any path given by FALCON_VERIFY_SO; ensure it points to a trusted) Tj
T*
(library or leave unset.) Tj
T*
(- Key storage is plain JSON on disk \(Keys/KeyManager_Public_Private_Keys.json\), not encrypted.) Tj
T*
(Backup/permission hardening is required.) Tj
T*
(- Verbose logging prints paths, key lengths, and sometimes previews; run with reduced logging in) Tj
T*
(production to avoid metadata leakage.) Tj
T*
(- Signing key delivery is now stdin/in-memory. Remaining exposure is process-memory lifetime and) Tj
T*
(debug/log mishandling, not temp-file residue.) Tj
T*
(- Verification accepts 1024-hex signatures in addition to 2048; if only Falcon-512 is intended,) Tj
T*
(tighten this to 2048 to avoid ambiguity.) Tj
T*
(- CLI path fallback includes shutil.which\("falcon_cli"\), but strict pinning plus file-permission) Tj
T*
(checks on required networks prevents untrusted binaries from passing verification.) Tj
T*
(- No hardware-key or MPC support; all signing uses the local CLI with full private key material.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Operational tips) Tj
T*
(- Keep falcon_cli versioned with the repo; update the version-bound digest map after audited) Tj
T*
(builds.) Tj
T*
(- Use FALCONCLI_SILENT=1 in production to cut noise; keep it verbose for diagnostics.) Tj
T*
(- Regenerate or migrate keys with KeyManager.enforce_cli_only\(\) if legacy formats appear.) Tj
T*
(- In CI, run a lightweight smoke test: python3 - <<'PY'\\nfrom Src.Accounts.falconcli import) Tj
T*
(FalconCLI\\nfc = FalconCLI\(\)\\nkeys = fc.keygen\(\)\\nsig = fc.sign\(keys['private_key'],) Tj
T*
('00'*48\)\\nassert fc.verify_transaction_hash\(keys['public_key'], '00'*48, sig\)\\nprint\('ok'\)\\nPY) Tj
T*
ET
